[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Reviewing test class setup**\n\nI need to ensure that top-level test classes are public, while helper classes can be public too. I’m wondering if we really need all these top-level test classes to only contain tests. The support class in the same package might trigger checkstyle issues. Should I add method type annotations? Java works fine without them, but checkstyle might indeed want a newline or some annotations like @Override? \n\nThere’s also the question of whether naming the public class \"UUMailer\" violates the one-to-one guideline; perhaps calling it \"TestUUMailer\" would be better for clarity.\n\n**Identifying native image issues**\n\nI’m seeing a potential issue with duplicate UUMailer definitions in the classpath. If there are two definitions, the native image might abort due to this duplication. Though Java typically doesn’t throw duplicate errors in the classpath, it could still warn us about it. \n\nAnother concern is the Class.forName call from EmailTask, which, if loaded by the same class loader, might cause trouble with package sealing if both EmailTask from the ant jar and UUMailer from test classes share the same package. I should check the ant manifest to confirm.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0372bc1e636ebc4c0169f586c743788196958a334dac02e838\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9YbPQOmyEZi1rs9wqshKRXRc3v7917W7fu8fPUnET84xiF2l32KkZxLctaJ06HUbIz5dRZvzQtSy6Xnaot88PNzMMfzOlZjvBrcV5x1H9XAH2GmpbWNoGOlUVKIs_eSkW6PKiL256GXpKC9REvXEz5rJVWopVgdsOtnj2npvduGZwRqw0r3AeBG-5hxvmI1jUa6k2UgUUu5EwFWjcUBKFfsGaVs7S1PpcFjawMjb37fMSaUFHLPnK7OG8qta7WcsET_0d1noOtKmai6R_piY_zHFuKhGob78WnM8OOa5st-tes3IQhkr8YMYvlGYN9twtkH9fz-W5MHJ8MeuUJvxE-l4jUHHxnFjVPnhg4HLut3RIamqtOR_azo5B_gq5IH47v9UXAzjzTOe_NwROSNhhOo7nLQ3u2B6dD6Ag-UNPutnrY_7Ck6X1P6NzsP44xGNClcmG7M9LJo1qYsuCgm4MXCVNkhS3xoBnV28zxmQNV2UlmUbaU9bduYvIfh33Oqd24GggEhHQJkjCEG7rqRJfB4WX